  "prompt": "What is automatic speech recognition?",
  "response": "Automatic Speech Recognition (ASR) is a technology that enables computers to convert spoken language into written text. Here are key details about ASR:\n\n1. Basic Function\n- Converts audio speech input into machine-readable text\n- Transforms human vocal sounds into readable words and sentences\n\n2. Core Technologies\n- Machine learning algorithms\n- Neural networks\n- Signal processing techniques\n- Natural language processing\n\n3. Key Components\n- Audio input processing\n- Sound wave analysis\n- Phoneme recognition\n- Language modeling\n- Word/sentence reconstruction\n\n4. Common Applications\n- Voice assistants (Siri, Alexa)\n- Transcription services\n- Closed captioning\n- Voice-controlled systems\n- Language translation tools\n\n5. Challenges\n- Handling different accents\n- Background noise interference\n- Understanding context and nuance\n- Processing multiple languages\n- Variations in speech patterns\n\n6. Performance Metrics\n- Word error rate\n- Recognition accuracy\n- Processing speed\n\n7. Advanced Techniques\n- Deep learning models\n- Contextual understanding\n- Continuous learning algorithms\n\nASR continues to improve with advances in artificial intelligence and machine learning technologies.",
